cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of game theory to combinatorial optimization problems related to packing, scheduling, and covering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making). The paper also involves the use of various machine models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The study of resource allocation and congestion control in networks could place it in cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture). Finally, the use of combinatorial optimization techniques could also make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
